headline: Delta earnings, consumer data, Fed: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories in the week ahead, including earnings results from companies like Delta Air Lines (DAL) and PepsiCo (PEP), the release of consumer sentiment data, and commentary from top Federal Reserve officials. After US lawmakers failed to agree on a spending bill on Friday, the government shutdown extended through the weekend. OPEC+ will also meet on Sunday, October 5. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
